1) Parent class for data downloading¶

In [1]:
class trading_strategy:
    
    def __init__(self, coin_name):
        import pandas as pd
        self.name = coin_name
        self.data = pd.DataFrame()

    def get_crypto_data(self):
        import pandas as pd
        import matplotlib.dates as mdates
        import quandl
        
        data_df = quandl.get(self.name, returns="pandas")
        
        data_df = data_df.ix[1:,]
        #data_df = data_df.set_index('Date')
        self.data = data_df
        data_df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data_df.index)
        self.date = data_df['Date'].apply(mdates.date2num)
        self.open = data_df.Open
        self.high = data_df.High
        self.close = data_df.Close
        self.low = data_df.Low

2.1.1) MACD Class¶

In [4]:
class MACD(trading_strategy):
    
    def __init__(self, coin_name, sma_f=20, sma_s=50, macd_f=12, macd_s=26, macd_sig=9):
        super().__init__(coin_name)
        self.sma_f = sma_f
        self.sma_s = sma_s
        self.macd_f = macd_f
        self.macd_s = macd_s
        self.macd_sig = macd_sig
        
    def calculation(self, sma_f=None, sma_s=None, macd_f=None, macd_s=None, macd_sig=None):
        import talib
        import numpy as np

        self.sma_f = np.where(sma_f == None, self.sma_f, sma_f)
        self.sma_s = np.where(sma_s == None, self.sma_s, sma_s)
        self.macd_f = np.where(macd_f == None, self.macd_f, macd_f)
        self.macd_s = np.where(macd_s == None, self.macd_s, macd_s)
        self.macd_sig = np.where(macd_sig == None, self.macd_sig, macd_sig)
        
        if self.data.empty:
            self.get_crypto_data()
                 
        self.sma_fast = talib.SMA(np.asarray(self.close), self.sma_f)
        self.sma_slow = talib.SMA(np.asarray(self.close), self.sma_s)
        self.macd, self.macdsignal, self.macdhist = talib.MACD(np.asarray(self.close), fastperiod=self.macd_f, slowperiod=self.macd_s, signalperiod=self.macd_sig)
        
    def plot(self):
        
        import pandas as pd
        import numpy as np
        import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
        #from matplotlib.finance import candlestick_ohlc
        from mpl_finance import candlestick_ohlc
        import matplotlib.dates as mdates
        import matplotlib.patches as mpatches
        from matplotlib import style
        
        if self.data.empty:
            self.get_crypto_data()
            
        self.calculation()
        self.strategy_result()
        
        ochl = np.array(pd.DataFrame(data = {'0': self.date,'1':self.open,'2':self.high,'3':self.low,'4':self.close}))
        df = self.data
        
        style.use('ggplot')
        fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
        fig.suptitle('Trading Strategy', fontsize=18, fontweight='bold')
        
        ax1 = plt.subplot2grid((10, 10), (0, 0), rowspan=6, colspan=10)
        cstick = candlestick_ohlc(ax1, ochl, width=.6, colorup='#53c156', colordown='#ff1717')
        ax1.plot(df['sma_fast'], c='blue',label = "SMA {0}".format(self.sma_f))
        ax1.plot(df['sma_slow'], c='yellow', label = "SMA {0}".format(self.sma_s))
        ax1.annotate('%0.2f' % df.ix[-1, 'close'], xy=(1, df.ix[-1, 'close']), xytext=(8, 0), xycoords=('axes fraction', 'data'), textcoords='offset points')
        
        buys = self.result['result'][self.result['result'] == 1]
        sells = self.result['result'][self.result['result'] == -1]
        ax1.plot(buys.index, self.result['close'].ix[buys.index],'^', markersize=6, color='m', label ='Buy')
        ax1.plot(sells.index, self.result['close'].ix[sells.index],'v', markersize=6, color='k', label ='Sell')
        
        ax1.xaxis.set_visible(False)
        ax1.set_title('Strategy: MACD for {0} \n P&L: ${1:,.3f} '.format(self.name,self.PL()))
        ax1.set_ylabel('{0}'.format(self.name))
        ax1.legend()

        ax2 = plt.subplot2grid((10, 10), (6, 0), rowspan=3, colspan=10, sharex=ax1)
        ax2.plot(df['macdsignal'], label = "macdsignal {0}".format(self.macd_sig))
        ax2.plot(df['macd'], label = "macd {0}:{1}".format(self.macd_f, self.macd_s))
        ax2.plot(df['macdhist'])
        ax2.fill_between(df.index, df['macdhist'], facecolor='#9999ff')
        ax2.xaxis_date()
        ax2.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'))
        ax2.set_ylabel('MACD')
        ax2.legend()
        
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.xlabel('Date Hours:Minutes')
        return(plt)
    
    def strategy_result(self):
        import pandas as pd
        
        self.calculation()
        df = pd.DataFrame(index = self.data.index)
        df['open'], df['close'], df['high'], df['low'] = self.open, self.close, self.high, self.low
        df['sma_fast'], df['sma_slow'], df['macd'], df['macdsignal'], df['macdhist'] = self.sma_fast, self.sma_slow, self.macd, self.macdsignal, self.macdhist
        self.data = df
        
        result = self.data[['close','sma_fast', 'sma_slow', 'macd', 'macdsignal', 'macdhist']].dropna()

        macdhist = result['macdhist']
        ma_f = result['sma_fast']
        ma_s = result['sma_slow']
        
        li = [0]*len(macdhist)
        li[0] = 0
        curr1 = 0
        curr2 = 0
        for i in range(1, len(macdhist)):
    
            if curr1 == 1 and macdhist[i] > 0:
                li[i] = 0
            elif curr1 == -1 and macdhist[i] < 0:
                li[i] = 0
            elif macdhist[i-1] < 0 and macdhist[i] > 0:
                li[i] = 1
                curr1 = 1
            elif macdhist[i-1] > 0 and macdhist[i] < 0:
                li[i] = -1
                curr1 = -1

            if curr2 == 1 and ma_f[i-1] > ma_s[i-1]:
                li[i-1] = li[i-1]
            elif curr2 == -1 and ma_f[i-1] < ma_s[i-1]:
                li[i-1] = li[i-1]
            elif ma_f[i-1] > ma_s[i-1]:
                if li[i-1] == 0:
                    li[i-1] = 1
                curr2 = 1
            elif ma_f[i-1] < ma_s[i-1]:
                if li[i-1] == 0:
                    li[i-1] = -1
                curr2 = -1

            if li[len(macdhist)-1] == 0 and curr1 == 1:
                li[len(macdhist)-1] = -1
            elif li[len(macdhist)-1] == 0 and curr1 == -1:
                li[len(macdhist)-1] = 1
        
        result['result'] = li
        self.result = result
        return(result)
        
    def PL(self):
        
        self.strategy_result()
        result = self.result
        
        df = result[result['result'] != 0]
        df = df[['close', 'result']]
        PL = [0]*(len(df)+1)
            
        quantity = [0]*len(df)
    
        for i in range(0, len(df)):
            if df.ix[i,'result'] == -1 and sum(quantity) > 0:
                PL[i] = df.ix[i,'close']*sum(quantity)
                quantity[i] = sum(quantity)*(-1)
            elif df.ix[i,'result'] == 1:
                PL[i] = df.ix[i,'close']*(-1)
                quantity[i] = 1
            elif sum(PL) <= 0 and sum(quantity) == 0:
                PL[i] = 0
                quantity[i] = 0
        
        if sum(quantity) > 0:
            PL[len(df)] = df.ix[len(df)-1,'close']*sum(quantity)
        
        return(sum(PL))

2.1.2) RSI Class¶

In [5]:
class RSI(trading_strategy):
    
    def __init__(self, coin_name, buy_all = True, rsi_up = 70, rsi_low = 30, rsi_period = 14):
        super().__init__(coin_name)
        self.buy_all = True
        self.rsi_up = rsi_up
        self.rsi_low = rsi_low
        self.rsi_period = rsi_period

    def calculation(self, rsi_up=None, rsi_low=None, rsi_period=None):
        
        import talib
        import numpy as np

        self.rsi_up = np.where(rsi_up == None, self.rsi_up, rsi_up)
        self.rsi_low = np.where(rsi_low == None, self.rsi_low, rsi_low)
        self.rsi_period = np.where(rsi_period == None, self.rsi_period, rsi_period)
        
        if self.data.empty:
            self.get_crypto_data()
                 
        self.rsi = talib.RSI(np.asarray(self.close), timeperiod=self.rsi_period)
    
    def plot(self):
        
        import pandas as pd
        import numpy as np
        import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
        #from matplotlib.finance import candlestick_ohlc
        from mpl_finance import candlestick_ohlc
        import matplotlib.dates as mdates
        import matplotlib.patches as mpatches
        from matplotlib import style
        
        if self.data.empty:
            self.get_crypto_data()
            
        self.calculation()
        self.strategy_result()
        ochl = np.array(pd.DataFrame(data = {'0': self.date,'1':self.open,'2':self.high,'3':self.low,'4':self.close}))
        df = self.data
        
        style.use('ggplot')
        fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
        fig.suptitle('Trading Strategy', fontsize=18, fontweight='bold')
        
        ax1 = plt.subplot2grid((10, 10), (0, 0), rowspan=6, colspan=10)
        cstick = candlestick_ohlc(ax1, ochl, width=.6, colorup='#53c156', colordown='#ff1717')
        ax1.annotate('%0.2f' % df.ix[-1, 'close'], xy=(1, df.ix[-1, 'close']), xytext=(8, 0), xycoords=('axes fraction', 'data'), textcoords='offset points')
        
        buys = self.result['result'][self.result['result'] == 1]
        sells = self.result['result'][self.result['result'] == -1]
        ax1.plot(buys.index, self.result['close'].ix[buys.index],'^', markersize=6, color='m', label ='Buy')
        ax1.plot(sells.index, self.result['close'].ix[sells.index],'v', markersize=6, color='k', label ='Sell')
        
        ax1.xaxis.set_visible(False)
        ax1.set_title('Strategy: RSI for {0} \n P&L: ${1:,.3f} '.format(self.name,self.PL()))
        ax1.set_ylabel('{0}'.format(self.name))
        ax1.legend()

        ax2 = plt.subplot2grid((10, 10), (6, 0), rowspan=3, colspan=10, sharex=ax1)
        ax2.plot(df['rsi'], label = "RSI {0}".format(self.rsi_period))
        ax2.axhline(y = self.rsi_up, color='green', linestyle='-')
        ax2.annotate('%0.2f' % self.rsi_up, xy=(1, self.rsi_up), xytext=(8, 0), xycoords=('axes fraction', 'data'), textcoords='offset points')
        ax2.axhline(y = self.rsi_low, color='blue', linestyle='-')
        ax2.annotate('%0.2f' % self.rsi_low, xy=(1, 40), xytext=(8, 0), xycoords=('axes fraction', 'data'), textcoords='offset points')
        ax2.xaxis_date()
        ax2.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'))
        ax2.set_ylabel('RSI')
        ax2.legend()
        
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.xlabel('Date Hours:Minutes')
        return(plt)
        
    def strategy_result(self):

        import pandas as pd
        
        self.calculation()
        df = pd.DataFrame(index = self.data.index)
        df['open'], df['close'], df['high'], df['low'] = self.open, self.close, self.high, self.low
        df['rsi'] = self.rsi
        self.data = df
        
        result = self.data[['close','rsi']].dropna()
        
        rsi = result['rsi']
        li = [0]*len(rsi)
        for i in range(1, len(rsi)):
            if rsi[i] >= self.rsi_up:
                li[i] = -1
            elif rsi[i] <= self.rsi_low:
                li[i] = 1
            else:
                li[i] = 0
                
        result['result'] = li
        self.result = result
        return(result)
        
    def PL(self):
    
        self.strategy_result()
        result = self.result
        
        df = result[['close', 'result']]
        PL = [0]*(len(df)+1)
            
        quantity = [0]*len(df)
    
        if df.ix[0,'result'] == 1:
            PL[0] = df.ix[0,'close']*(-1)
            quantity[0] = 1
    
        for i in range(1, len(df)-1):
            if self.buy_all == True:
                if df.ix[i,'result'] == -1 and sum(quantity) > 0 and df.ix[i-1,'result'] == 0:
                    PL[i] = df.ix[i,'close']*sum(quantity)
                    quantity[i] = sum(quantity)*(-1)
                elif df.ix[i,'result'] == 1 :
                    PL[i] = df.ix[i,'close']*(-1)
                    quantity[i] = 1
                elif sum(PL) <= 0 and sum(quantity) == 0:
                    PL[i] = 0
                    quantity[i] = 0
            else:
                if df.ix[i,'result'] == -1 and sum(quantity) > 0 and df.ix[i-1,'result'] == 0:
                    PL[i] = df.ix[i,'close']*sum(quantity)
                    quantity[i] = sum(quantity)*(-1)
                elif df.ix[i,'result'] == 1 and df.ix[i+1,'result'] == 0:
                    PL[i] = df.ix[i,'close']*(-1)
                    quantity[i] = 1
                elif sum(PL) <= 0 and sum(quantity) == 0:
                    PL[i] = 0
                    quantity[i] = 0

        if sum(quantity) > 0:
            PL[len(df)] = df.ix[len(df)-1,'close']*sum(quantity)
        
        return(sum(PL))

class MACD_RSI(trading_strategy):
    
    def __init__(self, coin_name, rsi_up = 70, rsi_low = 30, rsi_period = 14,sma_f=20, sma_s=50, macd_f=12, macd_s=26, macd_sig=9):

    def macd_result(self):
    
        macdhist = self.result['macdhist']
        ma_f = self.result['sma_fast']
        ma_s = self.result['sma_slow']
        
        li = [0]*len(macdhist)
        li[0] = 0
        curr1 = 0
        curr2 = 0
        for i in range(1, len(macdhist)):
    
            if curr1 == 1 and macdhist[i] > 0:
                li[i] = 0
            elif curr1 == -1 and macdhist[i] < 0:
                li[i] = 0
            elif macdhist[i-1] < 0 and macdhist[i] > 0:
                li[i] = 1
                curr1 = 1
            elif macdhist[i-1] > 0 and macdhist[i] < 0:
                li[i] = -1
                curr1 = -1

            if curr2 == 1 and ma_f[i-1] > ma_s[i-1]:
                li[i-1] = li[i-1]
            elif curr2 == -1 and ma_f[i-1] < ma_s[i-1]:
                li[i-1] = li[i-1]
            elif ma_f[i-1] > ma_s[i-1]:
                if li[i-1] == 0:
                    li[i-1] = 1
                curr2 = 1
            elif ma_f[i-1] < ma_s[i-1]:
                if li[i-1] == 0:
                    li[i-1] = -1
                curr2 = -1

            if li[len(macdhist)-1] == 0 and curr1 == 1:
                li[len(macdhist)-1] = -1
            elif li[len(macdhist)-1] == 0 and curr1 == -1:
                li[len(macdhist)-1] = 1
        return(li)
        
    def rsi_result(self):

        rsi = self.result['rsi']
        li = [0]*len(rsi)
        for i in range(1, len(rsi)):
            if rsi[i] >= self.rsi_up:
                li[i] = -1
            elif rsi[i] <= self.rsi_low:
                li[i] = 1
            else:
                li[i] = 0
        return(li)
        
    def strategy_result(self):
        
        import pandas as pd
        
        self.calculation()
        df = pd.DataFrame(index = self.data.index)
    
        df['open'], df['close'], df['high'], df['low'] = self.open, self.close, self.high, self.low
        df['sma_fast'], df['sma_slow'], df['macd'], df['macdsignal'], df['macdhist'] = self.sma_fast, self.sma_slow, self.macd, self.macdsignal, self.macdhist
        df['rsi'] = self.rsi
        self.data = df
        
        result = self.data[['close', 'sma_fast', 'sma_slow', 'macd', 'macdsignal', 'macdhist', 'rsi']].dropna()
        self.result = result
        result['macd_result'] = self.macd_result()
        result['rsi_result'] = self.rsi_result()
        
        macd_result = result['macd_result']
        rsi_result = result['rsi_result']
        li = [0]*len(macd_result)
        
        for i in range(1, len(macd_result)):
            if macd_result[i] == 1 and rsi_result[i] == 1:
                li[i] = 1
            elif macd_result[i] == -1 and rsi_result[i] == -1:
                li[i] = -1
            else:
                li[i] = 0
                
        result['result'] = li
        self.result = result
        return(result)
        
    def PL(self):
        
        self.strategy_result()
        result = self.result
        
        df = result[result['result'] != 0]
        df = df[['close', 'result']]
        PL = [0]*(len(df)+1)
            
        quantity = [0]*len(df)
    
        for i in range(0, len(df)):
            if df.ix[i,'result'] == -1 and sum(quantity) > 0:
                PL[i] = df.ix[i,'close']*sum(quantity)
                quantity[i] = sum(quantity)*(-1)
            elif df.ix[i,'result'] == 1:
                PL[i] = df.ix[i,'close']*(-1)
                quantity[i] = 1
            elif sum(PL) <= 0 and sum(quantity) == 0:
                PL[i] = 0
                quantity[i] = 0
            if sum(quantity) > 0:
                PL[len(df)] = df.ix[len(df)-1,'close']*sum(quantity)
        
        return(sum(PL))

3) Machine Learning¶

3.1) Class¶

In [18]:
class ML:
    
    def __init__(self, X = [], y = [], strategy_result = None):
        from sklearn.cross_validation import train_test_split
        if  X == [] and y == []:
            self.strategy_result = strategy_result
            self.X = strategy_result.ix[0:(strategy_result.shape[0]),0:(strategy_result.shape[-1]-1)].values
            self.y = strategy_result.ix[0:(strategy_result.shape[0]),-1].values
            self.X_trn, self.X_tst, self.y_trn, self.y_tst = train_test_split(self.X, self.y, test_size=0.30, random_state=42)
            
        else:
            self.X = X
            self.y = y
            self.X_trn, self.X_tst, self.y_trn, self.y_tst = train_test_split(self.X, self.y, test_size=0.30, random_state=42)
    
    def compute_lda(self):
        import pandas as pd
        from sklearn.discriminant_analysis import LinearDiscriminantAnalysis as LDA
        
        lda = LDA(n_components = 2)
        
        if len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==1]) > 1 or len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==-1]) > 1:
            lda.fit(self.X_trn, self.y_trn)
            y_pred = lda.predict(self.X_tst)
            self.model_lda = lda

            df = pd.DataFrame(data = {'test' : self.y_tst, 'predict' : y_pred})
            self.df_lda = df
        
            from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score
            self.accuracy_lda = accuracy_score(df['predict'], df['test'])
        
        elif len(y_tst[y_tst==1]) <= 1 or len(y_tst[y_tst==-1]) <= 1:
            df = pd.DataFrame(data = {'test' : [0], 'predict' : [0]})
            self.df_lda = df
            self.accuracy_lda = 0
        self.model_lda.fit(self.X, self.y)
        
    def compute_qda(self):
        import pandas as pd
        from sklearn.discriminant_analysis import QuadraticDiscriminantAnalysis as QDA
        
        qda = QDA()
        
        if len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==1]) > 1 or len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==-1]) > 1:
            qda.fit(self.X_trn, self.y_trn)
            y_pred = qda.predict(self.X_tst)
            self.model_qda = qda

            df = pd.DataFrame(data = {'test' : self.y_tst, 'predict' : y_pred})
            self.df_qda = df
        
            from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score
            self.accuracy_qda = accuracy_score(df['predict'], df['test'])
            
        elif len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==1]) <= 1 or len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==-1]) <= 1:
            df = pd.DataFrame(data = {'test' : [0], 'predict' : [0]})
            self.df_qda = df
            self.accuracy_qda = 0
        self.model_qda.fit(self.X, self.y)
        
    def compute_gnb(self):
        import pandas as pd
        from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB
        
        gnb = GaussianNB()
        
        if len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==1]) > 1 or len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==-1]) > 1:
            gnb.fit(self.X_trn, self.y_trn)   
            y_pred = gnb.predict(self.X_tst)
            self.model_gnb = gnb
    
            df = pd.DataFrame(data = {'test' : self.y_tst, 'predict' : y_pred})
            self.df_gnb = df

            from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score
            self.accuracy_gnb = accuracy_score(df['predict'], df['test'])
            
        elif len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==1]) <= 1 or len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==-1]) <= 1:
            df = pd.DataFrame(data = {'test' : [0], 'predict' : [0]})
            self.df_gnb = df
            self.accuracy_gnb = 0
        self.model_gnb.fit(self.X, self.y)
            
    def compute_svm(self):
        import pandas as pd
        from sklearn import svm as SVM
        
        svm = SVM.SVC(kernel='rbf')
        
        if len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==1]) > 1 or len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==-1]) > 1:
            svm.fit(self.X_trn, self.y_trn)  
            y_pred = svm.predict(self.X_tst)
            self.model_svm = svm
    
            df = pd.DataFrame(data = {'test' : self.y_tst, 'predict' : y_pred})
            self.df_svm = df

            from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score
            self.accuracy_svm = accuracy_score(df['predict'], df['test'])
            
        elif len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==1]) <= 1 or len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==-1]) <= 1:
            df = pd.DataFrame(data = {'test' : [0], 'predict' : [0]})
            self.df_svm = df
            self.accuracy_svm = 0
        self.model_svm.fit(self.X, self.y)
            
    def compute_rf(self):
        import pandas as pd
        from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
        
        rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_jobs=2, random_state=0)
        
        if len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==1]) > 1 or len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==-1]) > 1:
            rf.fit(self.X_trn, self.y_trn)   
            y_pred =rf.predict(self.X_tst)
            self.model_rf = rf
    
            df = pd.DataFrame(data = {'test' : self.y_tst, 'predict' : y_pred})
            self.df_rf = df

            from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score
            self.accuracy_rf = accuracy_score(df['predict'], df['test'])
            
        elif len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==1]) <= 1 or len(self.y_tst[self.y_tst==-1]) <= 1:
            df = pd.DataFrame(data = {'test' : [0], 'predict' : [0]})
            self.df_rf = df
            self.accuracy_rf = 0
        self.model_rf.fit(self.X, self.y)
            
    def result(self):
        
        self.compute_lda()
        self.compute_qda()
        self.compute_gnb()
        self.compute_svm()
        self.compute_rf()
        
        self.accuracy = {'LDA' : round(self.accuracy_lda*100,3), 'QDA' : round(self.accuracy_qda*100,3), 'GNB' : round(self.accuracy_gnb*100,3), 'SVM' : round(self.accuracy_svm*100,3), 'RF' : round(self.accuracy_rf*100,3)}
        
        return(self.accuracy)

4) Back testing¶

4.1) Class¶

In [24]:
from zipline.api import order, record, symbol, order_target
from zipline.algorithm import TradingAlgorithm
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

class backtest():
    
    def __init__(self, name, mname, data, quantity, start=200):
        self.name = name
        self.mname = mname
        
        from collections import OrderedDict
        import pandas as pd
        import pytz
        data1 = OrderedDict()

        data1['BTC'] = data
        panel = pd.Panel(data1)
        panel.major_axis.tz_localize(pytz.utc)
        
        self.data = panel
        self.quantity = quantity
        self.shape = data.shape[-1]-1
        self.start = start
        
    
    def initialize(self, context):
        self.context = context
        self.context.i = 0
        self.context.asset = symbol('BTC')


    def handle_data(self, context, data):
        self.context.i += 1
        if self.context.i < self.start:
            order(context.asset, 0)
        else:

            X = self.data['BTC'].ix[0:((self.context.i)-1),0:(self.shape)].values
            y = self.data['BTC'].ix[0:((self.context.i)-1),-1].values
        
            ml = ML(X,y)
            
            if self.mname.lower() == 'gnb':
                ml.compute_gnb()
                sign = ml.model_gnb.predict([self.data['BTC'].ix[self.context.i,0:(self.shape)].values])
            elif self.mname.lower() == 'lda':
                ml.compute_lda()
                sign = ml.model_lda.predict([self.data['BTC'].ix[self.context.i,0:(self.shape)].values])
            elif self.mname.lower() == 'qda':
                ml.compute_qda()
                sign = ml.model_qda.predict([self.data['BTC'].ix[self.context.i,0:(self.shape)].values])
            elif self.mname.lower() == 'svm':
                ml.compute_svm()
                sign = ml.model_svm.predict([self.data['BTC'].ix[self.context.i,0:(self.shape)].values])
            elif self.mname.lower() == 'rf':
                ml.compute_rf()
                sign = ml.model_rf.predict([self.data['BTC'].ix[self.context.i,0:(self.shape)].values])
            
            if(sign == 1):
                order(context.asset, self.quantity)
            elif(sign == -1):
                order_target(context.asset, 0)
            
        record(BTC=data.current(context.asset, 'price')) 
    
    def analyze(self, context, perf):
        import pandas as pd
        import numpy as np
        import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
        import matplotlib.dates as mdates
        import matplotlib.patches as mpatches
        from matplotlib import style
        
        style.use('ggplot')
        fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
        fig.suptitle('{0} Backtesting \n Model: {1} \n Total return: {2:0.5f}; Volatility: {3:0.3f}'.format(self.name.upper(), self.mname.upper(), perf['algorithm_period_return'][-1], perf['algo_volatility'][-1]), fontsize=15, fontweight='bold')
        
        ax1 = plt.subplot2grid((10, 10), (0, 0), rowspan=6, colspan=10)
        ax1.plot(perf['BTC'], label = "BTC", color='teal')
        ax1.annotate('$%0.2f' % perf['BTC'][-1], xy=(1, perf['BTC'][-1]), xytext=(8, 0), xycoords=('axes fraction', 'data'), textcoords='offset points')
        
        perf_trans = perf.ix[[t != [] for t in perf.transactions]]
        buys = perf_trans.ix[[t[0]['amount'] > 0 for t in perf_trans.transactions]]
        sells = perf_trans.ix[[t[0]['amount'] < 0 for t in perf_trans.transactions]]
        ax1.plot(buys.index, perf['BTC'].ix[buys.index],'^', markersize=10, color='m', label ='Buy')
        ax1.plot(sells.index, perf['BTC'].ix[sells.index],'v', markersize=10, color='k', label ='Sell')
        
        ax1.xaxis.set_visible(False)
        ax1.set_ylabel('BTC Price')
        ax1.legend()
        
        ax2 = plt.subplot2grid((10, 10), (6, 0), rowspan=3, colspan=10, sharex=ax1)
        ax2.plot(perf['algorithm_period_return'], label = "{0} return: {1:0.3f}".format(self.name.upper(),perf['algorithm_period_return'][-1]), color='orangered')
        ax2.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'))
        ax2.set_ylabel('{0}'.format(self.name.upper()))
        ax2.legend()
        
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.xlabel('Date Hours:Minutes')
        
        plt.show()
        
    def run(self):
        self.algo_obj = TradingAlgorithm(initialize=self.initialize, handle_data=self.handle_data, analyze = self.analyze,data_frequency='daily')
        self.perf_manual = self.algo_obj.run(self.data)
